{{DISPLAYTITLE:Line_SetAutomapFlags}} {{Special|281|lineid, setflags, clearflags|Miscellaneous}}
*''lineid'': The {{c|id}} of the line of which to set the [[automap]] flags. *''setflags'': The flags to be set. *''clearflags'': The flags to be un-set.
Changes the in-game flags used by the automap for the line with the {{c|id}}.
The flags are as follows (multiple flags can be combined by using the | character between the constant names): *'''AMLF_Secret''' (1): Line is a secret, so it is drawn as one-sided. *'''AMLF_DontDraw''' (2): Line is not drawn (hidden). This flag respects the setting of the {{c|{{CVAR|A|am_cheat}}}} and {{c|{{CVAR|A|am_showalllines}}}} console variables. This flag takes precedence over AMLF_Mapped and AMLF_Revealed. *'''AMLF_Mapped''' (4): Line is always drawn, whether it has already been seen or not. *'''AMLF_Revealed''' (8): Line is drawn as if revealed by a {{Class|MapRevealer|map revealer}}, such as the {{Class|Allmap|computer area map}}.
